article.headline: TCU's Shaw scored 19 points
article.linkText: No. 19 TCU rallies from 16-piont deficit to win
article.story:
ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Ebony Shaw scored 19 points, and No. 19 Texas
Christian rallied from a 16-point halftime deficit for a 69-66
victory Friday night over Saint Louis.

Tiffany Evans added 18 points on 7-of-10 shooting for the Horned
Frogs (12-2, 1-0 Conference-USA). Sandora Evans added 10 points and
13 rebounds.

Angie Lewis had 26 points for the Billikens (6-8, 0-1), and
Kirsti Holloway added 12.

En route to its halftime deficit, TCU was just 10-of-27 (37
percent), missing four of its six 3-point shots, while the
Billikens shot a marginally better 42 percent.

But in their second-half rally, the Horned Frogs made five of 10
shots from behind the arc, shot 48 percent overall and clamped down
on Saint Louis, forcing the Billikens to miss 19 of their 28 shots,
including all of their 3-point attempts.
